MARVELLOUS MAURY -ADOPTION PENDING 

PLEASE NOTE (January 6, 2021): Maury is available for adoption; we will take down the post once he is adopted. If you are interested in Maury we require a fully completed/signed adoption application as this is the first step. Please ensure that you read Maury’s full bio and meet all of the requirements we are asking before completing an application. Please go to our website at http://www.aarf-rescue.com/adopt/
to download our application or email us to request an application at deannaaarfrescue@yahoo.ca

Breed: German Shepherd
Sex: Male
Age: 8 years old
Size: Large
Health: Good Health, vet checked, fully vaccinated including rabies, flea treatments, fully dewormed, neutered, heart worm negative, full bloodwork panel done, dental scaling and polish and micro chipped
Adoption Fee: $500.00

Maury is an 8 year old male purebred German Shepherd Dog that has been fully vetted including neuter and is up to date on vaccines as well as microchipped.

Maury is a very lovable, gentle, outgoing guy who LOVES to play in the snow, chase snowballs and play fetch.  He is very affectionate and will allow you to handle his ears, feet, tail and face.  

Maury was never allowed to go upstairs or go on furniture in his previous home so a house with a lot of stairs would not be good for Maury at this time.  Eventually when Maury is comfortable in his new home, we think he will use stairs and not be so hesitant. 

Maury would be a wonderful walking companion and loves going for car rides  Maury knows his basic obedience commands such as come, sit, down, etc, but does needs some work on his leash and with his loose leash walking.

The ideal home for Maury would be calm and quiet, settled with a routine, lots of time for walks and to give him all the love and attention he desires.

YOU MUST MEET ALL OF THE FOLLOWING REQUIREMENTS to be considered to adopt Maury:

• No young children or grandchildren (an all adult home would be ideal)

• Previous dog experience

• May be good with 1 other mellow/laid back dog

• Someone that works from home/retired – someone who will NOT be returning to a workplace after COVID

• Fully Fenced in yard

- Must be 25 years of age and live in the Province of Ontario

If you are interested in Maury and think he may be the right fit for you please go to our website at http://www.aarf-rescue.com/adopt/
to download our application or email us to request an application at deannaaarfrescue@yahoo.ca

Hi, my name is Kady Lady Kady, in fact! I am a 10-month old, 55lb. female GSD/lab mix. I love meeting new friends; both other dogs and new people! I am quick to learn new skills and am responsive to training. Ive experienced only love and affection so Im looking for positive and gentle environment with my new family to teach me the social skills Ill need for a happy life.

The senior couple who rescued me at 3 months love me but need to focus on their own health and want me to be more active and learn skills with other young ones! They say I am calm and sensitive for my young age. They feed me plenty of bone-building food as Im growing so fast. I especially love playing ball and love being outside in the yard! Im looking for a home with another dog, preferably male, or a family with children as I would like to interact with others! I dont think I would be a good companion for extreme sports but would love a home or property with things to learn and a dog friend who wants to play and explore. Although I[m a growing pup I seem to be favoring one hip over the other, so I'm getting an xray Feb. 1st to make sure all systems are go. I've never been introduced to a cat, but with some training I'm pretty sure we'd get along. Can I join your family? I'm current on vacciantions, heartworm negative, microchipped and will be spayed soon. Miniumum adoption donation: $350.00

At only 18 months, Sherrie has had a rough start at life. As just a young pup herself, she is currently weaning her own puppies. animal.description:
Hi, my name is Nikia. I am around 5 months old and about 25 pounds. I am loving my new foster home. I am originally from Alabama and have been living with my Minnesota foster family since I arrived. We are having so much fun!

My favorite pastimes are playing fetch with my foster mom and hanging out with my foster siblings. Because I'm still a puppy, I can be a little overbearing for them as they are much smaller than me, but I would love a dog my size to play with! I do well in my kennel when my foster mom is busy or running errands and I seep in it at night. I do not mind my kennel, but I also like running around the house, playing with my toys and getting into mischief. My foster mom says I am a very busy puppy and need lots of attention until I get a little bit bigger. I like going on long walks but sometimes I am afraid to leave the yard because those big noisy cars scare me. I do well with my doing my pottying outside as long as I am kept on a schedule. The more consistent your with letting me out, the more successful I will be!

If you are looking for a very sweet and playful puppy, I am the one for you! Although I love my foster home, I am looking forward to meeting new humans and find my furever family soon. Maybe I can come home with you?



--------------------------------------------



All our Warrior Dogs will have all age appropriate medical care and vaccines, a microchip, and spay/neuter before adoption unless age is a factor with a puppy younger than 6-12 months at the time of adoption. If that is the case, the spay/neuter will be covered in the adoption fee and the owner will be responsible to have the procedure completed at a Warrior Dog Rescue Veterinarian at the appropriate time.

Please note that the majority of our dogs in rescue are from shelters where they have been found as strays or abandoned. Their breed description is based on our very best educated guess based on physical characteristics and their dispositions. If they came to our rescue as an owner surrender, the breed description will be listed as provided by the previous owner.

Adoption Fee - $525

To apply for this pup, please submit an Adoption Application at http://warriordogrescue.com/adopt/adoption-application/

If you would like to adopt a dog from Rescue Row please fill out an application at https://form.jotform.com/91767055990166 

*Please check your junk email folder if you do not receive a response from a Rescue Row member within 48 hours.

*You must live within an hour of the DFW Metroplex because we do trial adoptions and require a homecheck

*Our adoption fees are as follows (paid by cash or a check made out to Rescue Row):

 Dogs 12 weeks-6 months old: $300 adoption fee

 Dogs 7 months and older: $275 adoption fee

Rescue Row is a 501(c)3 (non-profit) all volunteer dog rescue organization serving the DFW Metroplex. We are dedicated to rescuing dogs in shelters, dogs in abusive or neglectful situations, and dogs surrendered by their owners because of difficult circumstances. We place dogs in loving, responsible, committed permanent homes, following a comprehensive adoption process, which includes taking considerable care in finding good matches and educating prospective adopters about the responsibilities and costs of bringing a dog into their homes and lives. Dogs in our care are spayed or neutered, microchipped, receive all appropriate veterinary care and treatment, and placed in nurturing foster homes while they await placement in their permanent homes. We assist dogs in distress without regard to age, breed or ease of placement. Dogs in the greatest need take priority. Finally, we strive to work with shelters and other rescue and humane organizations to develop a network of supporters and volunteers in order to create a better world for homeless dogs.

Meet Daisy! This girl is currently in a foster home and awaiting her forever home through PCPoundpuppies.She's a 3yr old black chihuahua/rat terrier mix. She currently weighs 16lbs and is spayed and UTD on all shots/vaccines. Daisy LOVES people. She wants to cuddle and be held all the time. Personal space is nonexistent. Once you start giving her belly rubs you're stuck as she'll constantly grab your hand and pull it back. She is friendly with other dogs as well as cats and respectful children. She eats twice a day on schedule perfectly fine alongside her doggie friend. She does fine on a leash and should get frequent exercise for her energy level. She's potty trained but will have an accident here and there, especially if she gets too excited. Daisy gets along with other dogs but will initially start growling (this only lasted a day upon meeting her bigger playmate). The two are now fine and cuddle with each other. Having a fenced in yard and being allowed on furniture would greatly benefit her in her new home. She's really just looking for a cuddle buddy.

She is currently in a foster home and all meet and greets are with an approved application. Yes, we do call your vet for a reference and we do verify what you put on your application so please be truthful.
A home with a tall fence (5 ft) is going to be a must for this girl since she enjoys running out the door when it's opened and we want her to be safe.
Her adoption fee is $150

Click here to submit an adoption application: https://pcpoundpuppies.webs.com/adoption-application
***IMPORTANT: Due to the effects of COVID-19, our Sunday adoption events at Pet Food Center have been canceled until further notice. If there is a dog you are interested in meeting, be sure to contact us and we may be able to set up a meet and greet as soon as possible.***
You can get in touch with us by email at pcpoundpuppies1@gmail.com or by phone at 812-483-4341 for more information.
We respond to inquiries and adoption applications at our earliest opportunity, but please be patient with us as we work full-time jobs and perform this service as volunteers. We do our best to return messages and schedule adoption interviews within a couple of days of receiving your application.
The fastest way to get the ball rolling is to complete an adoption application for the dog that caught your eye. Thank you for considering the adoption of a shelter dog!

animal.description:
Skylar has been with us for about two months now, and she continues to be the sweetest dog ever! She has all of the kids in the neighborhood wanting to come up and love on her because she is so non-threatening. Whenever we are out, she will set a course to cut people off, and then sit right in front of them looking for pets. Special people, and I am not sure what makes them special, get the full Skylar treatment, where she rolls over at their feet.

She does have some separation anxiety. She is doing much better being left, especially if the other pups are home with her. But, she is still a howling, whimpering mess when left totally alone. She sleeps in the crate, and can even be closed in it, when you are home, but she hates it in there if left in it while no one is home. A window perch so she can rest, while she is keeping an eye out for our return, has done wonders for her level of anxiety.

She is a bit mischievous...she is a little taller and can reach the edges of the kitchen counter. Skylar is very food motivated, and she dances around whenever there is a hint of food in the air. She will climb on chairs, tables, or reach up on counters for food. So care is required for normal food stuffs, as well as something she might think of as food, like granular fertilizer. She doesn’t really chew on things, but she does eat things the things she chews, especially stuffed dog toys.

Skylar still won’t willingly go out our back door onto the deck, which has the steps around the corner. We have to entice her with three pieces of kibble to get her out into the backyard. She will go out the front door, and she has no problem going out when she has visited other homes which have patio doors at grade. And speaking of going out the front door...if care isn’t taken, she will slip out to follow you.

She does well walking on a leash, and seems more interested in looking than sniffing. Except for when she sees a squirrel, she does not pull. She has about five dog friends on our little walk, and she would like to go up to their front doors every time. Excellent recall. But, a little tug to get her moving again is usually all it takes. So far, she hates wearing any kind of harness and will not leave the front sidewalk until I take it off.

She ignored the cats she spent a weekend with. All the neighborhood kids love her because she is so gentle and sweet, sitting right in front of them for pets. She loves sleeping on the couch or on her window perch during the day, and on the dog bed in the bedroom at night. She will hop into bed on occasion, and she is not too much of a bed hog.

Skylar is a sweetheart, with a naughty side, so she will keep you on your toes, that’s for sure. But then, the on switch goes off, and the light snoring commences. I think she would be a great fit for someone who wants a low exercise, high snuggle beagle.

Skylar's Webpage - http://beaglemaryland.org/brsm_ms/vIndividualCurrentDog.aspx?dogid=69869
Adoptable Dog Webpage - http://beaglemaryland.org/brsm_ms/vCurrentDogs.aspx

If you'd like to adopt one of our beagles:
*Go to our Website - href="http://beaglemaryland.org
*Review our  Standards for Adoption - http://beaglemaryland.org/Home.aspx?pg=standardsforadoption.htm
*Fill out an Adopter Profile - 
http://brsmbeagles.org/new_site/documents/BRSM_profile_secure.pdf
 and email it to us (or print it off, fill it in and send it via regular mail, if you prefer)
*A BRSM volunteer will contact you to guide you through the rest of the process!

We hope to hear from you, and so do the beagles!

animal.description:
Beacon arrived to us from a back yard breeder when they realized something was wrong.  Beacon and his sister Buoy, born 10/17/20, have been being treated for neosporosis, a  diseased passed along from the mom dog.  Beacon's hind legs are stiff, but he can still walk.  We do not know if he will be able to do steps or not.  NO APARTMENTS, FENCED YARD REQUIRED, LIMITED STEPS

Please visit www.handsheartspaws.org for an adoption application

All of our dogs are current on vaccinations, spayed/neutered, microchipped, fecal tested, heartworm tested, and they are all on heartworm and flea/tick preventative.

The adoption process is an application, a vet reference, a home visit, and a lifetime contract. The requested adoption donation for this dog is $400__.

We do not REQUIRE a fenced in yard (some dogs DO REQUIRE a fence.  Decide what is best for each dog), we do REQUIRE a means of safe outside containment.  We do NOT adopt to homes that use invisible fencing.  Invisible fencing is NOT a safe means of outside containment.

We are willing to adopt out-of-state, contingent on our ability to complete a home visit, but you must travel to Omaha to complete the adoption. We do not transport or ship our dogs.
animal.name: Beacon

I AM A TOUGH YOUNG CHIHUAHUA THAT HAS A BIG ATTITUDE. YOU WOULD TOO IF YOU HAD TO SURVIVE ON THE STREETS OF BAKERSFIELD. I DON'T KNOW WHAT THE FUSS IS ALL ABOUT. I LIKE TO BARK TO LET YOU KNOW I'M STILL HERE. I WANT A NICE HOME WITH A YARD I CAN PATROL. I WOULD LIKE TO CHASE SQUIRRELS AND MAYBE A FEW CATS JUST TO MAKE SURE THEY KNOW I'M THE BOSS. I LIKE SNACKS, PETS, AND I LIKE TO PROTECT MY OTHER DOG FRIENDS. I MAY BE TINY BUT MY MIGHTY 'TUDE MAKES MY SCARED FRIENDS FEEL SAFE. IF YOU WANT THE CHANCE TO BECOME PART OF MY POSSE FEEL FREE TO FILL OUT AN APPLICATION. IF I LIKE WHAT YOU HAVE TO OFFER I'LL CALL YOU TO ARRANGE A MEET!

http://www.wagsandwhiskerspetrescue.com/adopt.html

Thank you so much for looking into wags and whiskers for your next family member.

All of our pets are up to date on vaccinations, microchipped, heartworm tested if over 6 months old and will be spayed or neutered before being allowed to go home.

Unfortunately, we don't always know the background of each dog. Some were dumped, abandoned in an empty house, left tied to a tree, picked up by animal control as strays, or simply unwanted by their owners. We ask that only serious and committed adopters apply as these dogs have suffered enough.

If you are interested in meeting this pet please apply to adopt at
http://www.wagsandwhiskerspetrescue.com/adopt.html
if the pet is still available for adoption and you are approved to adopt we will contact you to set up a meet and greet appointment.

animal.description:
Bowie is a senior (born approx 11.1.12) neutered male Akita. He is up to date on vaccines, microchipped, on flea/heartworm prevention, house trained, crate trained, and leash trained.

Bowie came to us from the shelter in Suffolk, VA. He was surrendered by his owners for being "aggressive." Neither the shelter, nor us, have seen any overt aggression from him. We did get the impression that someone was not very nice to him as he was reactive and hand shy. He also had a lot of medical issues including low thyroid (which likely contributed to the aggression and anxiety), a massively enlarged prostate (ouch!), heartworms, and all the tick borne diseases. We have him on meds for the prostate and the thyroid and he has opened up so much. This kid is super mellow and affectionate, and super dog social.

animal.description:
Hi there...the name is Charlie. Life was a bit difficult for me the first few days at the shelter. My skin was itchy, my ears were achy, and I was a bit...er...crabby towards strangers. But thankfully, the nice folks here realized that between my move from a home, to the pound, to here and then with my skin and ears being ouchy (they made sure I saw a vet and have me feeling much better now), that I just needed a little more time to settle in. Now that I have, I really love people! I know that the volunteers are going to come in for walks, so I wait patiently for my turn and then we go on a walk and I'm told, I walk like a gentleman on leash (or at least I try my hardest). But my all-time favorite is when people come into my kennel and sit down, so I can cover them in kisses and lay my head on their lap for a quick snooze. I really hope someone can see past my dislike for other dogs and will give me a chance, because I really love people and can't wait to be your forever-cuddle-buddy!
.
.

All animals 6 months and older are spayed/neutered prior to adoption. Any kittens/puppies will have refundable spay/neuter deposits included in their adoption fee; spaying/neutering will be the responsibility of the adopter and a refund will be issued upon proof of the surgery being completed by the adopter's veterinarian of choice.
.
.
Kitten adoption fees are $150 (includes a $40 refundable spay/neuter deposit). Cat adoption fees are $120, unless otherwise noted. Dog adoption fees may vary between $200-250. Puppies adoption fees may vary between $300-350 (includes a $100 refundable spay/neuter deposit). All adoption fees are taxable (tax is not included in the prices listed above).
.

DOB: 5/2019 Weight: 60 lbs

Meet Zeta!
This sweet girl wouldn't look at the camera but kept looking for something..........
Maybe her pups that were just sold or given away? Maybe it is the family that she just lost?
She is a total sweetheart, about 1-2 years old and 60lb. She likes to play with toys and is good with other dogs but she doesn't like cats. She is house trained.
She loves people and is really confused about how she ended up at the shelter. Who can help this sweet girl to forget about her past and look forward to the future?
Her adoption fee is $150 and applications can be found on our website Pcpoundpuppies.com***YOU MUST FILL OUT AN APPLICATION BEFORE WE DO ANY MEET AND GREETS. QUESTIONS? CONTACT pcpoundpuppies1@gmail.com
Our adoption fee is $150 which covers a portion of the dog's vetting costs. The adoption process includes the completion of an application followed by an interview.
Click here to submit an adoption application: https://pcpoundpuppies.webs.com/adoption-application
***IMPORTANT: Due to the effects of COVID-19, our Sunday adoption events at Pet Food Center have been canceled until further notice. If there is a dog you are interested in meeting, be sure to contact us and we may be able to set up a meet and greet as soon as possible.***
You can get in touch with us by email at pcpoundpuppies1@gmail.com or by phone at 812-483-4341 for more information.
We respond to inquiries and adoption applications at our earliest opportunity, but please be patient with us as we work full-time jobs and perform this service as volunteers. We do our best to return messages and schedule adoption interviews within a couple of days of receiving your application.
The fastest way to get the ball rolling is to complete an adoption application for the dog that caught your eye. Thank you for considering the adoption of a shelter dog!

animal.description:
Grady arrived at Horse Creek Wildlife on October 16, 2020.  

He is a very sweet and handsome fellow.  He plays great with other dogs and loves spending time with people.  Grady is extremely affectionate and will take all the attention you are willing to give him.

He is a full-grown Terrier mix and he weighs 28 pounds.

Grady will make a great family pet!  He is anxiously waiting for a family of his very own!

All of our dogs are spayed or neutered and are current on all vaccinations. They are on monthly heartworm and flea/tick prevention. All of their medical needs are taken care of before they are available for adoption. Our adoption fee is only $100.00. Please complete an application, if you have found a dog you are interested in adopting. You can find our application at www.horsecreekwildlife.org/applic.html. Once completed, you can forward it to adoptions@horsecreekwildlife.org or fax it to 731-926-3000. Kim Austin, our adoption facilitator, will be in contact with you as soon as she has an opportunity to review your application. Understand that she has other duties and she will not ignore any interest shown in adopting one of our dogs. An application will need to be approved before a scheduled time to visit our dogs will be set up.  It may take up to 48 hours before she returns your call or responds to your email, due to work schedules, holidays and adoption events. We do the very best we can for the dogs we have rescued and do not take the adoption process lightly. Please be patient and understand that we will place our rescued dogs in the very best homes possible and reserve the right to refuse applications.

animal.description:
Stella is a 2 year old female Pit bull mix. She weighs 66 pounds. Stella and her friend Bricks were surrendered by their owner because unfortunately they were no longer able to care for them. This beautiful girl is the biggest sweetheart you will ever meet! She is very outgoing and loves to be with people. She also loves playing with her toys and running around the play yard. Stella is overweight right now but she is ready to work on her girlish figure! She will need exercise in her new home to maintain a healthy weight. According to her former owners, she is great with children. She is also dog friendly, seems to be housebroken and walks well on a leash.

animal.description:
"Hi, my name is Lobo. I am an 8 month old German Shepherd puppy and my new PACA foster found me running scared on Juan tabo around Nov 7th. I had no tags and no chip and had not been nuetered. I was limping and had a few long cactus quills stuck in my nose. Ouch! My foster was worried that I'd been hit by a car but the limp was because of that pesskie cactus that I had tangled with. After a trip to the vet I am now all better and am current on all my shots and am nuetered. At first I was very scared of my new home but my foster's dogs have helped me to learn new things like walking on a leash, going in the crate from time to time and commands like sit, stay, off and come.  Since I am a puppy I have alot of energy and I love playing with other dogs. I'm very smart and am also learning the word no when I try doing something I shouldn't. I'm still shy of strangers but we're working on that. I really like watching TV with my foster and my new fun thing to do lately is chewing on ice cubes. I really like the children that come to the house. I'm very loving and hope to go to my forever home soon."

PACA is a foster based rescue with no shelter to view our dogs.  We have temporarily stopped all our public adoption events due to COVID-19, however we are still placing dog into loving homes by private appointment with approved applications.  

Completed applications will be given to the foster to coordinate meetings as everyone feels comfortable.  This application helps us get to know you and your family a little better so we can find the perfect match! Application are found here:
http://nmpaca.org/images/pdf_files/PACA_Adoption_Application.pdf
Please email completed applications to pacadogs@aol.com 

All our animals are spayed or neutered, vaccinated, microchipped and tested for tic born illness and heartworm prior to adoption.  Our fee is $175.

animal.description: Rex, is a super fun, happy guy that definitely doesn't act his age. He's 7 years young and has oodles of love to give! He's been at PACC before, so we're hoping this is his last visit to the shelter. This time around, Rex had a few minor injuries, and was a model patient when getting fixed up by the PACC clinic. He definitely has some age related lumps and bumps, but nothing that's slowed him down even a little. This goofball recently got ahold of a soccer ball and frankly it was like watching the World Cup! Dribbling, passing, pouncing oh, is pouncing not part of soccer?? Rex says it is! When meeting other dogs in playgroup, Rex was appropriate and tolerant with greetings and generally kept to himself and explored the yard. Rex is a people- oriented guy and was very happy to get attention from the handlers. Come meet Rex today!

animal.description: Buddy (AKA Gaston) is an old friend ours here at PACC. Sadly it is not his first rodeo here but we love him and we are ready to find him a brand new home. Buddy's previous families had a lot of nice things to say about him. From his foster: he is housebroken and knows how to use a dog door. He is very polite in the house, never has accidents, doesn't jump on furniture and doesn't hurt anything. He greets everyone who comes to my house in a very nice and gentle way and everyone thinks he is very sweet. He loves long walks and to lie out in the sun. He does well with my chickens and loves to snuggle with me in my bed. His most recent adopter said that he did very well and was the perfect, happy gentleman at his home in a rural area, but when he moved to the city he had a very hard time adjusting and became anxious. Volunteers say that Buddy is a wonderful companion and he has always been a favorite for walkers. He is polite, curious, sweet and affectionate. He has all the love you could ever need and should be the only pupper in the home. Buddy has a hard time at the shelter and he really needs to get back into a comfy, safe home so that the can have the cozy retirement he deserves. Ask Buddy's volunteer advocate, Christy, about him: christy.holliger@gmail.com BUDDY IS ENROLLED IN THE GOOD DOG PROJECT AT PACC - Read a message from his case manager here: tinyurl.com/gdpmessage - Ask his case manager about him: rachel.jones@pima.gov

animal.description:
Jimmy came to Fox Valley Humane Society after his owner passed away. He is an old man looking for a relaxing home to retire to. He enjoys petting, and people that he connects with. He would love a home that can offer him affection and love, and a comfy couch to hang out on! Jimmy is on the smaller side of medium, only weighing 35lbs.

We always recommend crate training, exercise, playtime, and a regular schedule for potty breaks when bringing a new dog into your home. The shelter environment is much different than your home, so expect the unexpected. We do our best to help find the right pet for you, but your new dog may act differently on your turf than he/she did on ours.  Adjustment takes time for both you and your new family member, so remember to be patient and enjoy this new and exciting time!
Included in the adoption fee are rabies (if applicable) & distemper vaccinations, heartworm testing, deworming, spay or neuter surgery.

animal.special_needs_notes: Jimmy has a benign mass on his right shoulder. Previous vet records were obtained and this was found to be an infiltrative lipoma that had previous surgical removal attempted in 2018. The mass has since regrown. This is a type of benign fatty tumor, but the tumor has invaded into the muscle and while benign, still has the capability to grow over time. Removal with a boarded surgeon would be recommended if future adopters wish to perform surgery. Otherwise no surgical intervention with monitoring overtime is a valid option.

animal.description:
I will love you forever!Marley was born around January 7, 2019, and weighs about 50 pounds. Marley was surrendered to us by people who have surrendered several dogs in the past. Marley does fine with the other dogs and rides well in the car. His previous owner says that Marley is a snuggle bug and likes to play with toys. They also mentioned that Marley is gun shy and gets frightened when they pull out the BB gun to shoot at the rats. Marley was very patient with us on arrival while we were poking and prodding and checking him over. He seems to be a go with the flow type guy and will make an amazing companion. The Adoption Fee for this dog is $400.00
Adoptions fees vary based on adoptability. In general our fees include spay/neuter, all age appropriate vaccines, Home Again micro-chipping & registration, worming & flea control - a 'complete' pet. We accept CASH or Visa/Mastercard ONLY.

Joyful Rescues has no funding except for our adoption fees and miscellaneous donations. Pet care and vet bills are expensive - you must be ready to take on this financial (as well as emotional) responsibility. YOU MUST BE AT LEAST 25 YEARS OF AGE TO ADOPT A DOG FROM JOYFUL RESCUES

We keep our pet list as up-to-date as possible. As soon as a pet is adopted, it is removed from the list. If a pet is still showing, it is still available for adoption.

Can't Adopt Me? SPONSOR ME
Look for the Link 'Special Instructions to Seller' if you want to note a particular pet
Before you seek to adopt a pet from Joyful Rescues, please read our Pet Adoption page http://www.joyfulrescues.org/pet_adoption.html.

animal.description:
Age: 7yrs
Weight: 83lbs
Energy Level: Low
Overall Drive: Low
Location: Stanwood, WA

Bourbon is a lovable Velcro dog who is the low-key companion you’ve been waiting for. If he were a human, he’d be a retired flagger – always ready to patrol when needed, but currently just interested in relaxing and spending time with his family. Bourbon seems to be more fond of men than women, so might do best with a male primary handler.

Bourbon is great with people and other dogs and hasn’t had any issues with reactivity in his foster home. He loves walks and does well on a loose leash, even with distractions. He’s been known to cuddle and likes affection from those he trusts. Bourbon rides well in the car, has no reactivity issues around loud noises, and does well at the veterinarian’s office if he is muzzled. He is learning to be more comfortable alone and will often howl when left by himself, so he will need a family who can continue to work with him on reducing this behavior. Bourbon is non-destructive, fully crate trained, and has mastered basic obedience.

Bourbon’s ideal home would be a quiet one where he can spend plenty of time with his handler. He will occasionally get bursts of energy that are satisfied with quick play sessions, however, is mostly quiet and prefers to just be near his person. Looking for that perfect retirement partner to warm up your winter? Bourbon is your guy!

WEST COAST ADOPTIONS ONLY

Our adoption process includes- completion of an application, followed by a telephone interview. If that goes well, we will arrange for a home visit.
Adoption Fee: $500.00. Transport along Interstate 5 (Bakersfield, CA to Bellingham, WA) is available but cost not included in adoption fee.

Please visit www.woofproject.org and fill out an adoption application located here https://www.woofproject.org/application

animal.description:
Age: 1yr
Weight: 70lbs
Energy Level: Moderate
Overall Drive: Low
Location: Vancouver, WA

Kenzo thinks he is a lapdog, despite his 70-pound frame! He is a loyal companion and partner who wants nothing more than to be beside his handler. He is very sensitive and willing to please, and bonds to those around him quickly. If he were a human, Kenzo would be an apprentice – he is young, curious, and still gaining confidence but is always eager to learn new things.
While Kenzo is affectionate and sweet with those he is familiar with, he is aloof with strangers. He will check in with his handler when a stranger approaches to see how to react but will usually warm up quickly with proper introduction. 

Kenzo has high prey drive and thus will not be suited for a home with small children or animals. He is very interested in other dogs and gets very excited when he sees them. He needs slow, guided introductions with dogs as well given his shy nature and tendency towards uncertainty but is friendly, submissive, and sweet when allowed to meet others on his own terms. Kenzo rides well in the car, has done well at the veterinarian’s office, and is mostly unfazed by loud noises. He will need a handler comfortable with moderate correction including some redirection when he becomes distracted. Kenzo is working on basic obedience and being calm in his crate during the day.

Kenzo will excel as an active companion to someone who can dedicate time to working with him as he continues to grow and mature. Once he builds trust with his new family, he will likely be a great adventure buddy for someone who is prepared to be a patient, yet firm. Kenzo’s focus and desire to please would make him a great candidate for formal obedience or a water-based sport like dock diving. This student is looking for his perfect teacher – Kenzo is ready to be your protégé!

WEST COAST ADOPTIONS ONLY

Must have previous or current, purebred Malinois experience OR other high drive working breed experience

Our adoption process includes- completion of an application, followed by a telephone interview. If that goes well, we will arrange for a home visit.
Adoption Fee: $500.00. Transport along Interstate 5 (Bakersfield, CA to Bellingham, WA) is available but cost not included in adoption fee. 

Please visit www.woofproject.org and fill out an adoption application located here https://www.woofproject.org/application

animal.description:
Apollo is a sweet boy that is LOVES children! He has high energy but still loves to be a couch potato. So if you're looking for a dog that you can take on walks and play with who will also enjoy sitting on the couch watching tv with you, Apollo is your guy! Apollo would like to go to a home without any small animals or cats in the home. Apollo is selective with other dogs so he may enjoy going to a home with canine pal.

Apollo would like to live in a house rather than an apartment, and he takes a little while to adjust to a new routine, for this reason it will be important for him to have time to decompress in the home environment. He has great leash manners and appears to be housebroken.

We always recommend crate training, exercise, playtime, and a regular schedule for potty breaks when bringing a new dog into your home. The shelter environment is much different than your home, so expect the unexpected. We do our best to help find the right pet for you, but your new dog may act differently on your turf than he/she did on ours.  Adjustment takes time for both you and your new family member, so remember to be patient and enjoy this new and exciting time!
Included in the adoption fee are rabies (if applicable) & distemper vaccinations, heartworm testing, deworming, spay or neuter surgery.

animal.description: My name is KORA LOU and I'm a sweet 1.5 yr F Blue Pitbull. I'm a petite 50 lbs of PURE DARLING BUD! I was found running in the streets of Brooklyn saying hello to everyone big and small!. I'm super friendly, lively and loving. I'm still a young girl,  so I'm pretty active and I need daily structured exercise and discipline. I'm good on leash and I know basic commands .. but am a great student as I'm eager to please and quick to learn. I'm good with dogs in passing, but I'm a little too excited with small dogs so I could be with a tough small dog or a large dog and preferably a silly goofy male!  I've not lived with a cat so not sure how I would be with a cat but I've met them outside and didn't chase them but squirrels are a different story!! I'm CRAZY about balls!!!.. I love to fetch them and try to pop them if it's a soccer or basket ball...don't walk me by a basket ball court as I will want that ball and never leave! When I'm at home I'm a total snugglebug lap dog and I'm very well behaved. I would love to be with someone that will take me on lots of outdoor adventures and be their co-pilot!! If that's you...

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Thank you for considering adopting one of CARA's Special pets! To apply read about our adoption policies
here
to fill out an application.
Good day to you friends. I am Berwin. A lot of you have probably heard of me already. When CARA brought me in I had come from a very bad situation. I had a broken jaw, which was not fixed, and it healed that way to where my mouth couldn't close. It caused me a lot of pain and made it very hard for me to eat. When I came to CARA you fine folks that support this rescue donated a lot of money so I could have a better life, and I had surgery to remove half my bottom jaw. When I went for my surgery they also found BB's under my skin, so everyone found out that more things have happened to me then they already knew. Well, the good news is I have now healed up from my surgery. I really enjoy being able to eat food without pain, and I am getting use to using my bottom jaw again. The better news is I am now allowed to be adopted, so I am looking for someone amazing out there who wants to give me the love I should of always received. I do have one request. I would really need a home with no cats. I am not their biggest fan, and hoping that someone out there is ok with that. Please put in an application and once it is approved they will set up an appointment for you to come meet me. Hope to be seeing you soon.To see more animals for adoption, please visit the CARA Website

Our adoption fees are:
Dogs: $155
Cats: $95
Puppies under 4 months: $115 plus S/N Deposit: $100
Kittens under 4 months: $70 plus S/N Deposit: $100

All pets available for adoption have been spayed or neutered (unless under 4 months please read about our adoptions
here
), are current on vaccinations and preventatives, and micro-chipped. Cats have been tested and confirmed negative for Feline AIDS and Leukemia. Dogs have been tested for heartworm disease.

Our shelter is located at 42 Deep River Rd in Sanford and is open Tues, Thurs, & Fri from 3pm - 7pm & Sat from 10-2pm (other times available by appointment). CARA's adoption process and online application can be found at
http://www.cara-nc.org/info/adoption

Please call 919-774-9433, email adoptions@cara-nc.org, or visit www.cara-nc.org for information about this or other pets available for adoption.

If you would like to adopt me or any of my friends, please visit CARA to fill out an on-line application or e-mail us at adoptions@cara-nc.org.

Every animal that comes into the CARA program is here because one or more events occurred that led to this animal needing not only a home, but a person or family to love and protect them. Each animal has been loved and cared for by a small and determined group of people who want nothing more than to know each animal is safe for the rest of his or her life. Thank you for looking to adopt!

Cadillac was surrendered to a rescuer after suffering abuse from his former owner. Adore was contacted to help with vetting him and finding him a home, so we agreed. Cadillac seems to be good with dogs larger than him, but he is not good with small dogs or cats. 

Cadillac is about 1-2 years old and weighs close to 45 lbs. He is neutered, up to date on vaccines, and microchipped.

Email us at info@adorehouston.org if you would like to foster or adopt Cadillac!

You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Clipper and Willow are a bonded pair that we would like to place together. They are with a family in San Francisco and have been for a few years, but the family has come upon some difficult times and would like to place Clipper and Willow ideally with someone who would love to take them on daily long walks, hikes and they would love to go camping.

Willow is a beautiful bi-eyed girl who is about 4 years old and weighs about 60 lbs. Willow is extremely eager to please and listens very well and is incredibly smart. She has perfect recall and is easy to have off leash. She has a little bit of separation anxiety, but she has done fine being left alone in the house with Clipper. She sometimes will cry/husky howl if left tied up outside a store or in the car. She really wants to just be close to her human all the time. She does great in the car. Loves to run and play with all other dogs and will even cuddle up next to you on the couch if allowed. She's great with other dogs , although she would probably prefer that it just be her and Clipper in your home. Between her and Clipper she is the boss and sometimes takes his toys and treats. He is mellow so he just lets her do what she wants. She has many endearing qualities, including the husky talking and just general sweetness.

animal.description:
This is Jazzy, available at Dog House Adoptions in Albany area. We have had the opportunity to play and spend time with Jazzy the last few weeks and are excited to share her profile. Jazzy is 4 years old— the perfect age! She’s out of puppyhood, but loves being active. She is extremely responsive to cues and really eager to learn. Jazzy loves exploring and running in open areas. She is looking for an adopter who will take her on adventures and give her the quality time she deserves. Her family would need to help her practice calming indoor activities, after she has a nice walk of course! 

Jazzy knows how to sit, lay down, touch, look, stay, leave it, and more! Completely potty trained, up to date on vaccines, and spayed. She is just a sweetie and will snuggle up to you immediately. 

Management will be important at first since she is very playful; you’ll have to keep desirable items like shoes and underwear off the floor! She seems to be good with both men and women; would do best as the only pet in the home; and although she is okay with kids, would prefer a no kid home. Families with older children with experience should still inquire. Jazzy enjoys meeting new people but a house without lots of excitement is best. 

Email her rescue to apply: pawsomepupspersevere@yahoo.com
animal.name: Jazzy

Hi, I'm Harrison! I'm an energetic, playful guy with lots of love to give! Medical staff saw that I had something in my chin, and they ended up pulling out a bullet with a few pieces of my fractured jaw. However, this doesn't phase me, and I'm almost fully healed! My ideal home will have a fenced in yard for me to zoom around in, and have an active lifestyle. I will benefit from lots of positive reinforcement training and exercise. Right now I can only have things that are soft- like soft toys and treats- until I'm fully healed. Ask an adoption counselor to meet with me today! 



Busy BeeI'm a naturally playful, curious, and trusting canine. Take me for a big walk every day; give me something to do. After my job's done, I'll curl up in front of the fire with you in the evenings. I'm a dog on a mission to please you and myself.

animal.description:
This is Oden. He is a 1 year old, 35lb, male, German Shepherd mix. Oden is great with other dogs, however he is very shy with new people. He needs a forever home willing to work with him on building confidence and that will be patient with him, as well as continue his training. He is crate and potty trained, and will require a fenced in yard. He has not been tested with children, however they are not recommended due to his timid nature. He does like to chase, which includes his foster home cats and horses. He is neutered, UTD on vacc., microchipped, and kept on monthly flea/tick/hw prevention. To apply to adopt visit
www.handsofhoperescue.com/adoptapp
.
Oden's adoption fee is $250. All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. This dog is fostered in Hays, KS and adopter must drive to pick up. We do not ship or deliver. We do allow out of state adoptions, however qualified in state applications will be given preference. Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. To learn about Hands of Hope Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at HandsofHopeRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

animal.description:
**Due to COVID-19, all meet and greets will be by appointment only. Please call us at 604-275-2036 to set up an appointment.**

PERSONALITY: Bumble came into the Shelter through no fault of her own. Bumble is a very high energy, fun loving, sweet girl. She loves getting attention and cuddles from her human friends. She also loves playing with toys and has no problem keeping herself entertained - she is known for chasing shadows and light, like a cat.

We have come to learn that Bumble is under socialized with dogs and because of this has reactivity when seeing and meeting most dogs. Bumble also has prey drive - so no small dogs or small animals in the home with her. We are looking for an active home with a calm, confident handler that has experience with dog reactivity and is willing to work with Bumble on her socialization and manners.

Bumble is also a very strong, bouncy girl that can be rather high strung, therefore we are looking for a home with no small children - 12 years or older.

Due to BSL we are hoping to find a home for Bumble outside of Richmond and Burnaby as she hates wearing a muzzle. She has been spayed, microchipped and vaccinated with us. 

LIKES: Cuddles and attention.
  
DISLIKES: Being alone.
  
AGE: Just over a year old.
 
If you are interested in Bumble, you can call our shelter at 604-275-2036, or email us at info@rapsbc.com to book a Meet & Greet.

animal.special_needs_notes:
Bumble has a limp on her right hind leg, and after being assessed by our veterinarian and being checked over by an orthopedic specialist, it was determined that she will need surgery on the leg.
We are requesting that when applying to foster her, you have this in mind. After her surgery she will need strict crate rest (as she is getting here at the shelter), short, leashed walks only for bathroom breaks, will be on medications, and will have a few trips to the vet that the foster will help with.
All post-surgical care will be shared with the foster of course and we will help with any questions regarding Bumble's recovery journey.

We are setting up adoptions with approved adopters on an appointment basis. We are no longer hosting adoption events at PetSmart until further notice. We are not arranging meet and greets; but appointments to finalize adoptions to limit exposure for all. Our adoptions come with a one week trial period in which if things are not working out, we will refund your adoption fee if you decide to return your newly adopted Faithful Friend. Our adoptions must be done in person and we do not arrange transport to adopters. Our adoption fees vary and we are only able to accept payments by card* at this time but include spay/neuter, heartworm test (dogs), FeLV/FIV test (cats), age appropriate vaccines and deworming, flea, tick and heartworm medication and microchip.

Teddy came to us from a horrible hoarding situation and was heart worm positive. Several dogs coming out of that hoarding situation have had a wide variety of broken bones, we are assuming due to malnutrition. We are working on strengthening his bones. We don't foresee any broken bones in his future, but want to disclose all we can about his past. As Teddy's heartworm treatment is complete, he is learning how to be a dog. Teddy is not housebroke and is learning how to play, he has recently figured out that the soft toys are fun to toss in the air. If you have an abundance of patience and would like to see a dog become a pet and learn how to play and not be fearful of humans, this is your chance. animal.description:
Hi! My name is Tucker aka Tux! My family uses both names and I have already figured out that's me! I was a stray on the streets for several months before animal control finally grabbed me I hated the shelter and shut down there and sadly no one ever came looking for me. Then I was rescued and from there, there's so much to tell you about me, I hardly know where to start so here goes

My mom says if she didn't already have 4 dogs of her own, she'd be keeping me (she said she also doesn't want daddy to leave her)! The vet says I'm about 18 months old, so I still have alot of puppy energy! So I need a home that has time for me. I think I'm going to start with the things mom says make me more challenging at times - which is a short list! I need some work on leash manners - I do awesome and walk pretty well until I see another dog - then I get overly excited and want to meet them. Mom says it's not aggressive at all, it's just excitement that gets crazy. I'm very food motivated though, so treats to distract and reward are definitely helping me focus! Just today, after 4-5 training treats (and lots of praise), I successfully passed three dogs with only a few episodes of losing sight of my mom! Mom was super proud of me! We are still exploring the best leash to help me redirect my attention.
Mealtime is super exciting for me!! Mom tried once to leave me out of my crate while she was getting food bowls ready and decided that wasn't her best idea (of course that was shortly after I got here too!). I did figure eights around the kitchen and living room in excitement while she chased me down. I thought it was great - my mom wasn't as excited about it. So now I know to just go right in my crate when she tells me to and I sit and wait for her to make breakfast and dinner! The crate scared me at first and I didn't like it, but as I said, I'm food motivated so mom would toss a treat in the back of the crate for me and I'd go right in!! I'm even beginning to know how to sit and 'leave it' (for a few seconds) when mom puts my meal in my crate. I do talk to her when I'm in thereI'm just excited to eat!! :) When I'm done eating though, I'll wait quietly for mom to let me out while everyone else finishes their meal. Let me be clear - this is the ONLY time mom has to crate me! My dad is working from home and can let me out during the day, but I've NEVER had an accident in the house and I've even scratched at the door in the middle of the night asking to go out a couple of times. Mom leaves the door to the crate open though, and occasionally now she'll find me sleeping in there!

I am going to daycare with my brothers and sisters and they say I jump right in and start playing!! I absolutely love daycare and I pass out when I get homeI play hard while I'm there! I have loved all my 15 year old skin brothers friends that come in and are super loud alot and of course they love me too! I sleep through the night in a dog bed next to my mom. I do crawl into bed though and she laughs at me because she's never seen a dane lift the covers and burrow himself under them and fall asleep COMPLETELY buried like I do!! It really makes me happy, so if there's room in your bed, I'd really love that! I can play pretty rough at times, so I'd love another dog to run and wrestle with! Mom thinks young kids probably wouldn't be the best for me since I don't really know my puppy strength and size when I'm running and playing. She doesn't want me to accidentally hurt a little one in the house. And like most danes, I just sit wherever it looks comfortable even if there's already someone sitting there! lol

I already have mastered sit and shake!! We're working on down and stay and I'm making progress, but still need just a bit more time to conquer those! I just take off when mom tries to wipe my feet, but if she encourages me, I'll let her do it when it's necessary! When I first got here, I would jump on mom and whoever else came in the door I rarely do that now, as I realize I only get love and attention when I don't. I'm a fast learner for certain!! Mom also thinks it's hilarious that when she goes in the garage to leave, I run upstairs to the 2nd floor bonus room and she can see me watching her leave with my snout pressed on the window!!

Sooo, basically I'm about a perfect family member! My mom thinks I'm the 'cat's meow' BUT... I may be the cat's meow but I need a home with NO cats as that is the one thing I am not good with. I hope you'll consider me in your search for the newest addition to your home!

https://greatdanefriends.com/tucker

Please contact Great Dane Friends (info@greatdanefriends.com) for more information about this pet.

*****Great Dane Friends of Ruff Love covers NC and surrounding states for adoptions. We require a fenced yard (exceptions made on a case by case basis - NO exceptions for puppies or deaf/vision impaired dogs - no invisible fencing), that stairs in the home be covered with some sort of slip resistant material to prevent injury, that all other animals in the home be up to date on vaccinations as well as spayed/neutered and that all dogs live inside as a part of the family. Our approval process consists of an application, vet and reference checks, phone interview and house check. Please email us for an application or if you have any questions.*****

animal.description:
Gemma is a sweet, calm but timid German Shepherd. She came from a Southwest KS shelter. She needs someone who is willing to give her time and space to adjust in a new loving home. 

I'm not sure how she ended up at he local shelter but my guess is she was an outside only dog or a farm dog and finally wandered off. She is very head shy and will cower if approached quickly. She has gotten more comfortable over time since she has been with us

She was originally afraid of the leash and didn't want to come inside, but now she leashes and walks well, she is also comfortable in her kennel.

She has never made a mess in her kennel. We have not been able to see what she does around cats but at the previous shelter she seemed fine with dogs(mainly just ignored them). 

Gemma is looking for her second chance, I think once she is comfortable in her new surroundings she will make an amazing dog. She just needs the right person to give her a chance. 

If interested in Gemma please send an email to hoisingtonvet@gmail.com

animal.description:
Brewster T. is a sweet 9-year-old male German Shepherd Dog who was surrendered by his owner to a shelter in Southern California. His owner lost his home and could no longer provide for Brewster. Brewster was emaciated and confused about what was happening. At the shelter he was friendly and sweet despite the many changes he was going through. Brewster has some arthritis but he enjoys walks and walks well on leash. Brewster is reserved but is eager to get attention and engages well with people. He is well mannered, house trained, gets along peacefully with other dogs and rides well in the car. He shows no food aggression or other difficult behaviors. Brewster needs a family to give him the stability and love he craves!

Brewster T. Summary:
- Brewster is a male, 9 yrs old, weighs 65 lbs, current on shots
- Good with Adults, dogs, and travel in the car
- Children & Cats TBD

Brewster passed a set of evaluation tests before being accepted into the TSGSR. The tests are not intended to assess how smart the dog is but are important for TSGSR to determine if the dog is expected to be safe in a family home. The tested behaviors check to see if the dog will guard or protect food or toys from people, will tolerate handling all over its body (including ears, nose, lips to check teeth, lifting paws, belly, back, and gently pulling the tail) and the ability to get along with other well behaved dogs. He remained calm during all of these tests and showed no aggressive tendencies. 

Please join us in welcoming Brewster to TSGSR! Check back often. We will be updating his bio as we learn more about him!

What's Next for Brewster T:
Thulani Senior German Shepherd Rescue (TSGSR) will continue to see that Brewster is well cared for and receives all medical care needed for his well being while in our care. In addition, TSGSR is beginning a search for an adoptive home that will care for him for the rest of his life. He will come to his new home with a supply of food, a cushy pad if wanted, and other goodies such as toys. 

Brewster is a younger senior. As such there is no adoption fee but limited medical coverage. Please talk to the TSGSR staff about the coverage.

If you want to learn more about Brewster, or are interested in possibly providing an adoptive or foster home, please send us a message by clicking on the "Ask About Me" button. We will often get feedback or "updates" from a dog's foster home and as any updates become available they will be included here.

If you are reading about him on Petfinder.com sometimes an available YouTube video is not listed. If this occurs you can still view the video by pasting its URL into a new browser window or tab.

Available Video URL(s): https://youtu.be/W4DIj-s0nTc

Saving one dog wont change the world. It will change the world for that one dog.

animal.description:
Looks like: Border Collie/Aussie
Male, 14 years old, 34 pounds

This handsome and sweet boy is looking for an adopter. He was once called Davie, but is now known as Kupuna. This is because in Hawaii, the wise elders are known as Kupuna, which are the honored ones, deserving of respect and special care like this guy needs and deserves. Despite his frailty, he has a depth of spirit and resilience that has inspired everyone he's met. He was emaciated and unable to walk when brought in and yet he quickly made major improvements. However, he is unlikely to ever be able to go on walks or otherwise be active. Thankfully, he is very affectionate and loves to be gently petted and be around people. He is a very sweet and loving guy. His mobility issues are due to spinal arthritis but he can get around a home decently despite a hunch in his back. He gets along well with other dogs and has an overall docile personality. 

Kupuna's ideal weight is 40 pounds and he is doing some physical therapy to help his mobility. He is also completely deaf and struggles with fecal incontinence due to lack of control of his hind end. Kupuna will need a very special home. He is a wonderful, loving dog who follows his person around the best he can but his energy level is pretty low and that's reflected in all aspects of his behavior. He needs an adopter who will accommodate his condition. One where he will be given the care he needs, excellent food and a lot of affection. He will not do well with stairs, hyperactive or pushy dogs, and probably no young children. He is a quiet boy looking for a calm home. 

Davie came to us from Hitchcock Road Animal Services after being surrendered by his guardian who could no longer care for him.
animal.name: Davie aka Kupuna

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Gucci Gucci Susan Lucci! This little diva is Gucci and she lives up to her name! She is a beautiful 1.5 year old chihuahua and she weighs about 5 pounds. Gucci hails from Texas and she was getting a little too big for her britches there according to her owner. They were about to send her to a shelter when we intercepted to get her to NY!

Gucci is a chihuahua lover's dream! She is very sweet to her foster mom and loves to sleep on her neck when it's nap time. Initially she would growl at the other dogs in the house but that soon stopped. Now she sleeps along side of them. She LOVES cats - LOVES!! She is so excited when she sees one and gives it kisses non-stop. She is crate trained and will often go inside for a nap. We were told she was guarding a crate and items in Texas but we haven't had that issue here. She has actually become playful with the other little dogs in the house. We think the stress of losing her home and the journey here could have been the issue. Gucci is a typical chihuahua with her potty habits - it's when she feel like going outside, she goes. Other then that, she uses the potty pads pretty consistently. She does have a fully fenced yard in her foster home. Gucci loves treats and will sit very nicely to get one. Gucci is not overly friendly with new people but when she knows, she is a loyal dog to her person. Since she is so small, we prefer no large dogs in her future home. We will also prefer older kids 12+ at least. Gucci would love a home that has chihuahua experience as they can be quirky little dogs - especially the tiny ones!

Gucci is spayed, up to date with vaccines, microchipped, flea/worm treated and tested neg. for heartworm. Her adoption fee is $400

animal.description:
Meet Honey! 
Honey is a 10 year old chi mix. Last year he was seized from his owner as part of a cruelty case that the city was persuing. After months of waiting his fate, we finally were told he gets to live the rest of his life knowing LOVE! We are excited to see Honey have his happy ever after. 
Honey is crate trained and will vocalize when he needs to go potty. He loves walks and has started to play with the other dogs in his foster home. Some of his favorite activities is sunbathing, laying in laps and sleeping under the covers. He is also great with cats. Honey does have a heart murmur but at this time it does not require any medication or medical intervention. While Honey may be shy to open up at first once he does he is a lover! 

To set up a meet and greet or inquire about a dog, please first fill out an application at https://savinghoperescue.org/contact. It doesn't obligate you, but it is the first step. We don't get to all of the inquiries but respond to all applications. Thank you for choosing to rescue!

Mia is a beautiful three-year-old Alaskan husky mix who adores human attention and companionship.  Mia is spayed, up-to-date on vaccinations, and is housetrained; now she just needs a new home and family of her very own!  Mia is looking for a family that understands she is a working breed dog with high energy and an active mind that requires stimulation.  She will need plenty of physical and mental exercise to keep her content in her new home.  She is very sweet and loving and did fantastic on her temperament test.  She would be okay with older children who have been taught how to properly interact with dogs. 

 Mia has a high prey drive so she would not be good with cats or small animals.  She is dog-neutral (non-aggressive, non-reactive towards other dogs, but prefers them to stay out of her space). Mia prefers to be the only pet in the home.    

If you are interested in meeting Mia, please fill out the online adoption application found here (please copy and paste this URL into your browser): https://forms.gle/CWMLcZzSSqvBUgWe7

animal.description:
On Nov. 26th an estimated 8 month old (DOB 3-29-20) black and white male Pitbull was brought to Northwood on emergency. He  had jumped off a 3 foot wall and landed poorly the day before.  He immediately came up lame in the right rear leg.  He was still not willing to use the right rear leg at all at time of exam.  Radiographs showed fractures of the right tibia and fibula at the level of stifle/knee. The owner relinquished him so he could get the surgery he needed.  We named him Ham Bone (the name fits). Ham Bone was treated for internal and external parasites.  He was also vaccinated.  Ham Bone had surgery 12-3-20 to cross pin the avulsed piece of bone at the top of his tibia.  Surgery was difficult as the surgical site had fibrosed in and the avulsed piece of bone was so fragile that it broke into small pieces.  The surgeon finally got some degree of reattachment to the damaged bone then he placed the leg in a cast to restrict Ham Bone’s movement on the tenuous repair.  The day after surgery, Hambone started vomiting and having diarrhea.  A parvo test was positive.  Hambone was treated for Parvo and did well.  Within 2 days Hambone was eating again, doing well. He is neutered and ready to be adopted. Now this goof ball is ready for his forever home.

Name: Hambone
Species: Canine/ Pitbull
Gender: Male/Neutered
Birthday: 03/29/20
Current Location: Northwood Animal Hospital
Minimum Adoption Donation: $100

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Riza!  I'm a 2 1/2 year old girl who weighs 50lbs.  I am looking for someone to take me home and call me their own!! I LOVE people--I'm a social butterfly who gets along with new people and gets excited to make new friends. I would snuggle all day long if you'd let me! I have lived with young children before and am very good with kids. I have also lived with cats, and although I'm known to chase them from time to time, I can live peacefully with them.  While I can meet some dogs politely, I do not do well with all dogs, and I can be protective of my things and would do better living as the only dog in my new home. I'm not protective with people though--I'm super gentle :)  I get a little anxious when left alone so would do best with someone who can spend more time with me. I'm crate trained though which helps with acclimation big time! I  ride well in the car, too!

If you are interested in meeting this pet, please call 541 474 5458 for an appointment. All appointments are made by phone for the most up to date availability of the pets and the schedule. Thank you.

animal.description:
**Thank you to Tammy who donated towards Kitty's care!**

MY STORY: Kitty came to CBHS from a partnering animal rescue organization and is being treated for heartworms at Cedar Bend Humane Society. 

AGE: Approximately 2 years.

TRICKS & COMMANDS: Sit

ABOUT KITTY: Kitty can be a little shy when you first meet her, but it doesn't take long for her to warm up and show you how sweet she is! She loves attention and will happily take a treat and "sit" for you. 

Kitty is an all-around pretty calm girl, but she gets excited when playing with toys and enjoys playing outside in the snow. Kitty would do best in a home as the only pet so she can soak up all the love that her new family will give her!

Adoption fee includes spay/neuter, vaccinations, worming, microchip, and a start on flea/tick prevention.

For more information, please call CBHS adoptions at 319-232-6887 or email at adoptioncounselor@yahoo.com.

animal.description:
Please only send inquires to the email in this bio all others will not be answered. Please read the bio before sending questions - we answer all we know about the dog here.

Izzy's looking for her forever home She was left on her own wandering around a Good Samaritan reached out to Heidi's Legacy to help find her forever home. We think she's between 6 and 7 months old and she weighs under 50 lb. We don't think she's going to get much larger.
She loves to run and chase the ball. She enjoys her crate and sleeps through the night. She only barks when she sees dogs or cats...mostly because she wants to play with the dogs We're not really sure what she wants to do with the cat. She needs to work on walking on a leash , not counter-surfing and taking treats but these things can be taken care of when you do the obedience training .

Izzy's Adoption fee is $400 - obedience training is required

Obedience training is also required for all our pups. We understand with what is going on in the world that this may be a bit delayed. Please email us the completion certificate.

To apply to foster or adopt please fill out application at

www.heidislegacydogrescue.com/apply-to-foster-or-adopt

Thank you for completing the application. We are all volunteers and short on time, we will contact you back only if we have more questions or your application is approved and you will be invited to meet the dog. We apologize for not being able to answer everyone back.

For more information contact Kelly.V@HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

DOGS are in Foster Homes. There is NO shelter.

**Our companions MUST live in your home as part of your family.**We do not transport.

**See our website for more information. www.HeidisLegacyDogRescue.com

All communication is thru email so please be patient with us. We are all volunteers and work full time jobs and have families of our own.

It takes anywhere between 3-7 days to process an application - the more complete the application the easier it is for us to process it. Please notify your vet that we will be contacting them and to release information to us.

ADOPTION PROCESS:

1. Complete this application
www.heidislegacydogrescue.com/apply-to-foster-or-adopt

***Everyone must submit an application - we only keep them on file for 1 month

2. Application background check, vet check, etc

3. Invitation thru email to meet the dog(s).

4. Adoption Contract

animal.description:
Rodger is a 2 year old chocolate lab mix who weighs 65 lbs.  He has a ton of energy when he runs outside, but once he's tired himself out, he's usually calm inside.  Roger is quite intelligent and extremely interested in pleasing his human(s).  As a result, he has already improved his behavior in most areas.  He sits when told, stays in the back seat of the car, and waits on his leash to go out until the garage door is fully open.  Rodger loves car rides, playing in the snow, and squeaky toys.  He craves cuddles, hugs, and just being close.  Rodger still has some challenges -- he pulls on his leash (although less so over time), and sometimes barks at other dogs when on a walk.  Rodger would do well with a fenced in yard, since he's super fast and a very athletic runner, at times performing gymnastic style jumps!  If you're looking for a playful and loyal buddy who is very affectionate, and you're willing to put some effort into a fast learner, Rodger would be perfect!

animal.description:
This is a courtesy listing only for Goldie. This Doxie is NOT at Oregon Dachshund Rescue, Inc. 

Meet Goldie -

Goldie is an adorable 10 year old  neutered male dachshund. He is a real love and so appreciative to be saved. He is extremely overweight needs vetting and a full dental with extractions.  We are partnering  with dachshund rescue of Los Angeles. Any questions please contact ODR Jenell at  jrangan@comcast.net. More information in the near future. 

If you or anyone you know can help, please share this email or contact Jenell at jrangan@comcast.net 

Please note,  this is a Courtesy Listing for a doxie that is NOT at Oregon Dachshund Rescue, Inc. We are helping the owner find his/her new forever family. Oregon Dachshund Rescue, Inc. has posted this dog as available for adoption or rescue intake as a courtesy accommodation to the dog's owner. Any and all information, photos, etc. have been provided by the dog's owner. Oregon Dachshund Rescue, Inc. is not responsible for the accuracy of any of the information contained in this listing or any information that may have been omitted. Thank you!

ODR, INC. ADOPTION CRITERIA (aka Our Fine Print):
Based on 30 years of experience with rescue doxies, we have pretty strict criteria for dogs that we adopt and that we recommend to owners whose doxies we list courtesy posts for, the sole aim of which is to facilitate a successful adoption with a forever family. 

*Do you work from home/stay at home/work part time?  
*Have a securely fenced yard? 
*We do not place same gender dogs in a home unless they were raised together, and *Children need to be 12 or older (some exceptions IF the dog is a puppy or the child has been raised with a doxie). 
*We prefer non smokers and a home with no other small animals (ferrets, hamsters, etc). *Cats are on a case by case basis depending on the dog. 

Remember these are rescues, many were surrendered because of these or similar issues.

Thank you!

animal.description:
PHOTOS:  Virtually all of our dogs have online PHOTO ALBUMS through SmugMug with LOTS of additional pictures.  Just copy and paste the link below into your browser (or simply type it in) and then search for the dog's "gallery" by name

          http://adoptasleddog.smugmug.com

VIDEOS:  In addition to photo albums, almost every dog has a video which will give you a much better "feel" for his or her personality.  NOTE:  In the new Petfinder format, it has become quite a bit more difficult to find and to play videos.  Please PAGE THROUGH the photos, looking for a photo overlaid in the center with a "play" arrow inside a circle.  This icon is white, so it can be difficult to see. 
 In many (most) cases, the video is the last photo displayed as you page through.  Just click on that photo and it will play.  Please make sure you CHECK ON THE PETFINDER VIDEO ICON, above, to see a video of this wonderful dog!  Our videos will include, at a minimum, whatever info we had on the dog upon (or shortly after) his/her arrival into our program.  There will sometimes be video updates as well.  And in every case, our Adoptions Coordinator can be emailed at ADOPTASLEDDOG@AOL.COM to answer questions and provide the most current information we have on the dog.  

NOTES:  Please see video or contact our Adoptions Coordinator at ADOPTASLEDDOG@AOL.COM.

ADOPTION DONATION:  $250  Before adoption, all Northern Lights dogs (regardless of whether Petfinder's symbols appear) are spayed or neutered, microchipped, heartworm negative, fully vaccinated and tested/treated for known parasites.
 
WHAT TO DO IF YOU WANT TO ADOPT THIS DOG:  Email us at ADOPTASLEDDOG@AOL.COM to request an application and get started.  WE DO NOT HAVE AN ONLINE APPLICATION - you will have to request one via email.  We will review your application to determine if there is a good fit between you and/or your family and this dog.  We may suggest another dog or dog(s) if we can offer a better fit in terms of lifestyle, experience, other pets, etc.  A vet check, reference checks, and a home visit will be conducted before an adoption can be considered for approval.  
 
NORTHERN LIGHTS DOES NOT HAVE A PHYSICAL SHELTER.  We are a nonprofit rescue organization comprised of individuals who open their private homes to foster dogs in need of a second chance..  When fosters are not available, we often pay to board a dog until space is available.  New fosters and donations to pay for boarding are always desperately needed us.  Email us at KATYLIED2@AOL.COM if you are interested in donating or for information on fostering.
 
FAQ:  For information regarding our organization, as well as adoption policies and practices, please visit our Petfinder Home Page at WWW.NORTHERNLIGHTS.PETFINDER.COM.
 
 
NOTICE:  In the vast majority of cases, the dogs in our program and rescued from shelters, and Northern Lights has no means by which to collect or verify a dog's history.  We work in concert with our veterinarians, and breed and age estimates are based on a combination of professional input and our collective experience.  Our policy with information acquired prior to acceptance and while the dogs are in our care is that of "full disclosure".  It is our goal to ensure the adopter has all available information to ensure the best possible match between the dog and the adopter(s).  If we have identified a behavioral or health condition while the dog is in our care and custody, every effort will be made to correct it prior to adoption, OR the adopter will be made aware of the issue or condition prior to adoption.  Northern Lights' screening process is designed to identify only those adopters who are willing, and have the means, to treat conditions which may occur after adoption, and the adopter will be contractually responsible for doing so. However, Northern Lights' policy is to accept any adopted dog back into the program, at any time, for any reason.

My name is Zaidee. I'm a 1 year old Labrador mix. I am a little reserved and shy. It takes time for me to adapt to new situations, environments, and people. I'm looking for a patient family who will give me the opportunity to adjust to my new home. Once I warm up to you, I'm a total sweet heart who likes to cuddle and play. I would do best in a home that offers me encouragement and positive reinforcement; Make sure to bring the whole family in to meet me if you're interested. I can't wait to find the perfect family who will help me blossom!

From: Owner Surrender

animal.description:
My name is Ella, and I'm the perfect combination of energy and cuddles. I may be 7 years old, but I am still active and like to play for those who like a more active lifestyle. On the flip side, I'm very good at relaxing at home and snoozing on the sofa. 
I currently live in a home with two other older dogs. We have all gotten along fine once we were slowly introduced. You see, I can get a bit nervous with new situations and dogs I don't know, so I'd do best with someone who is patient and can help me gain more confidence. My foster mom says I'm extremely well behaved at home and very much house trained. I walk well on a leash most of the time...I love walks...and I can get a little excited and pull when I see another dog, squirrel or deer. I've been working on controlling my excitement, and I need someone to continue to help me with this.
According to my previous owner, I've lived in only one home since I was a puppy, so all this change is new for me. Sometimes it can be scary, but I'm a pretty happy girl most of the time. I like to be with my people rather being left alone, so I'd do best if I wasn't left alone for long periods of time. If you think you might have the right home for me, please contact my foster mom at ncfosterdoggies@gmail.com. I have a lot of love to give and just want someone to love me like crazy! Primary Color: Black Weight: 45lbs Age: 7yrs 2mths 2wks
animal.name: Ella
